                 ----------- Functions ------------- 
 Function is a block of reuseable code that perform a specific task or set of tasks.Functions are use to organize code into modular and mangeable pieces, promote code reuse, and makes program more readable.
   
   function function_Name(Parameter){
          //execute code 
          return result        //optinal return statement
   }

1.function declaration
  function sum(){

  }

2.function invoketion
  sum();

3. function Parameters
  function sum(name){
    console.log("hello" + name)
  }

4. function experession : 
   The Javascript Function Expression is used to define a function inside any expression. The Function Expression allows us to create an anonymous function that does not have any function name which is the main difference between Function Expression and Function Declaration. 
  
  Function expression:- 
          let result = function sum(name){
                 console.log("hello" + name)
          } 
          result("JavaScript")
  
  Anonymous Function expression:- 
          let result = function (name){
                 console.log("hello" + name)
          } 
          result("JavaScript")
  
  Arrow Function expression:- 
          let result = (name) => {
                 console.log("hello" + name)
          } 
          result("JavaScript")

5. Anonymous function
    It is a function that does not have any name associated with it. Normally we use the function keyword before the function name to define a function in JavaScript, however, in anonymous functions in JavaScript, we use only the function keyword without the function name.
   
   Anonymous function
            let result = function(name){
                 console.log("hello" + name)
            }
            result("JavaScript")


6.immediate innvoke function
 (function(name) {
    console.log("hello" + name)
 })("JavaScript");



7. fat arrow function
   const sum = (a, b) =>{
    var c = a + b;
    console.log("Addition of two number : "+ c)
   }

   sum(5, 10);




8.Reverse a string using function 

const strreverse = (str) =>{
  let reverse = "";
  for(let char= str.length - 1; char>= 0; char--){
    reverse = reverse + str[char];
  }
  return reverse;
}
console.log(strreverse("Yogesh"))